        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q25403"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q2934"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q670498"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q7368"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q830"/>
        <ontology:hasEntity rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/resource/Q95010"/>
        <ontology:isPresentedBefore rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N23_VC_21_ES/event/ev3"/>
        <ontology:is_identified_by rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/appellation/Mountain_landscape_and_reference_chains"/>
        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N23_VC_21_ES"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/43.166666666_-2.166666666"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/1"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The reference mountain chain of this VC is Cantabrian Mountains. The reference mountain landscape of this VC is Bidania-Goiatz. Bidegoian is the highest municipality in the historical territory of Gipuzkoa. Surrounded by farmhouses, forests, and mountains, among which Ernio (1,075 m) stands out. Bidegoian has managed to maintain the essence of rural Gipuzkoa. Also, this isolation has contributed to the preservation of the natural environment that surrounds the municipality in perfect condition. The pigs take care of the beech forest. They graze in the meadows, together with sheep and cows and goats on steep terrain.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


